  "history": {
    "en": "Developed in the 19th and early 20th centuries from various European terriers, such as the Jack Russell and Fox Terrier, brought to Brazil by immigrants. These dogs were crossed with local Brazilian farm dogs, creating a unique breed adapted to the country's environment and standardized as a farm and small game terrier, recognized by the FCI.",
    "zh": "19世纪至20世纪初，由移民带入巴西的各种欧洲梗犬（如杰克罗素梗和猎狐梗）培育而成。这些犬与当地巴西农场犬杂交，创造出适应该国环境的独特品种，并标准化为农场和小型猎物梗犬，获FCI认可。"
  },
